Over Easy Eggs

Ingredients (Serves 2)
	•	2 large fresh eggs
	•	1 1/2 tablespoons (20 g) unsalted butter
	•	1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt
	•	A few drops sherry vinegar or lemon juice (optional)

⸻

Method
	1.	Heat Pan & Butter
Preheat a nonstick skillet over medium-low. Add butter and swirl until melted and lightly foaming; milk solids should turn pale golden, not brown.
	2.	Add Eggs
Crack eggs into the pan, spacing apart. Season immediately with salt.
Cook until whites are opaque and edges lightly crisp, yolks still domed.
	3.	Flip
Using a thin spatula, carefully flip each egg.
	4.	Finish
Cook the second side 20–30 seconds only. Remove from heat.
Finish with a few drops of vinegar or lemon juice, if using. Rest 1 minute and serve immediately.

⸻

Optional Enhancements
	•	Use refined olive oil instead of butter for dairy-free
	•	Finish with cracked black pepper or chives
	•	Spoon a little foaming butter over whites before flipping for extra sheen
	•	Serve over toast, sautéed greens, or alongside potatoes

If you want this adjusted to over-medium, basted, or cooked in cast iron, say the word.